OL,3,CUK has 'tropical night' as record for
OL,4,Cwarmest May evening broken
OL,6,FThe hottest May temperature could be
OL,7,Fbroken again on Tuesday, with an
OL,8,Fexpected high of 35C across large
OL,9,Fswathes of southern England and Wales,
OL,10,Fwhich could even creep up to 36C.
OL,12,FThose forecasts span the Midlands, the
OL,13,Fsouth-east and south-west of England,
OL,14,FEast Anglia and South Wales, according
OL,15,Fto forecasters.
OL,17,FThunderstorms could be sparked in the
OL,18,Fafternoon, which will affect how hot
OL,19,Fit gets, the Met Office added.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
